articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of Palestinians fled the northern Gaza Strip on Saturday ahead of an expected Israeli ground assault, while Israel said it kept two roads open to let people escape.
articles.title: Israel and Hamas at war: Latest news

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of people attended pro-Palestinian rallies in Australian state capitals on Sunday despite police threats to curb them, amid tensions after the bloody Hamas incursion into Israel eight days ago.
articles.title: Pro-Palestinian rallies in Australia over Gaza draw thousands

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanese Hezbollah fighters launched a missile at an Israeli northern border village on Sunday, killing one person and wounding three others, the militant group and Israeli medics said.
articles.title: One killed, 3 wounded in cross-border Hezbollah attack on northern Israel

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The death toll in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank reached 2,383 Palestinians dead and 10,814 injured on Sunday morning, according to Palestinian health ministry sources.
articles.title: Gaza and West Bank death toll reaches 2,383 Palestinians - ministry

articles.author: Humeyra Pamuk
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken will meeting Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman in Riyadh on Sunday, a U.S. official said, as Israel prepared to launch a ground assault in the Hamas-controlled Gaza Strip.
articles.title: Blinken to meet Saudi Crown Price on Sunday in Riyadh, US official says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel's communications minister said on Sunday he was seeking a possible closure of Al Jazeera's local bureau, and accused the Qatari news station of pro-Hamas incitement and of exposing Israeli soldiers to potential attack from Gaza.
articles.title: Israeli communications minister seeks shutdown of Al Jazeera bureau

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia plans more flights to repatriate citizens from Israel after plans for two flights were cancelled on Saturday, Foreign Minister Penny Wong said, but they depend on concerns about security.
articles.title: Australia plans more repatriation flights from Israel, subject to security issues

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israeli troops prepared on Sunday for a ground assault on the Hamas-controlled Gaza Strip as the country hit back for an unprecedented assault on its territory, and Iran warned of "far-reaching consequences" if Israel's bombardment was not stopped.
articles.title: Gaza braces for Israeli ground assault, fears of conflict spreading grow

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: As Israel prepared on Sunday for a ground assault on the Hamas-controlled Gaza Strip, Palestinians who have lost numerous family members in air strikes were bracing for more destruction if Israel hits back on an unprecedented scale on its territory.
articles.title: Gaza residents who have lost family fear more destruction as ground assault looms

articles.author: John Foley
articles.description: JPMorgan’s (JPM.N) boss serves his quarterly earnings with a side of brimstone. The mega-bank Jamie Dimon runs is performing strongly, and yet he openly frets and rants about what’s coming: higher interest rates, smothering regulation, recession, war. The pessimism is something of a schtick that doubles as an asset.
articles.title: Jamie Dimon makes anxiety a feature not a bug
